data.name: Zschimmer & Schwarz: Personal Care
data.description:
Competence from top to toe: when it comes to personal hygiene, quality cannot be compromised. And this is precisely the philosophy of Zschimmer & Schwarz: our versatile products for skin and hair care, cosmetics and toiletries produce guaranteed results for a well-groomed, beautiful and colorful life. We offer customers all over the world tailor-made chemical specialities which are precisely fit to meet their requirements and the demands of their target groups.


If you wish to find out more about our products and services, please contact us – we are more than happy to answer your questions!

data.name: SYNTRAN
data.description: SYNTRAN® branded consumer specialty polymers are designed so that formulators may create value and differentiate their products within the Personal Care marketplace including Sun Care, Skin Care, Hair Care, Cosmetics and Toiletries. Syntran Polymeric Opacifiers have been specifically designed for use in personal care products. They impart a milky white appearance in products such as shampoos and conditioners, and bath and shower gels. They deliver improved performance and convenience at a lower total formulation cost. Syntran Opacifiers offer formulators increased flexibility to produce a superior end product with a balance between appearance and cost.

data.name: SYNTRAN® 5778
data.description:
SYNTRAN® 5778 is based on a patented bimodal technology with film forming properties. This unique interpenetrating network with two different ionic structures increases the adhesion, decreases the setting time, and still allows a controlled removability without compromising the good water resistance.

According to the application and the objective the SYNTRAN® 5778 can be used between 5 and 70 percent.

data.name: SYNTRAN® 5762
data.description:
SYNTRAN® 5762 is a film-forming material providing benefits in many applications. Through a proprietary polymerization process with a selection of functional groups, ZSCHIMMER & SCHWARZ INTERPOLYMER’s technology improves the properties of adhesion, cohesion, gloss, flexibility, dispersion, and water resistance.

The film formers offered by ZSCHIMMER & SCHWARZ INTERPOLYMER are used in a wide range of cosmetics and skin care products by many international companies. Depending on the application and the objective, SYNTRAN® 5762 can be used in a formulation at a level of 5 to 70 percent.

data.name: SYNTRAN® 5760CG
data.description:
SYNTRAN® 5760CG is a film-forming material providing benefits in many applications. Through a proprietary polymerization process with a selection of functional groups, ZSCHIMMER & SCHWARZ INTERPOLYMER’s technology improves the properties of adhesion, cohesion, gloss, flexibility, dispersion, and water resistance.

The film formers offered by ZSCHIMMER & SCHWARZ INTERPOLYMER are used in a wide range of cosmetics and skin care products by many international companies. Depending on the application and the objective, SYNTRAN® 5760CG can be used in a formulation at a level of 5 to 70 percent.

data.name: SYNTRAN® 5900
data.description:
SYNTRAN® 5900 is a water-based emulsion that modifies the visual appearance of personal care products from clear to opaque without affecting the other desired properties of the formula.

SYNTRAN® opacifiers give whiteness and density at significant low levels (from 0.1 to 1.0 percent as supplied) with excellent formulation stability.

SYNTRAN® 5900 is slowly added to the base product under agitation at the end of the manufacturing cycle (i.e., after final adjustment). A stability control is recommended.

data.name: SYNTRAN® 5905
data.description:
SYNTRAN® 5905 is a water-based emulsion that modifies the visual appearance of personal care products from clear to opaque without affecting the other desired properties of the formula.

SYNTRAN® opacifiers give whiteness and density at significant low levels (from 0.1 to 1.0 percent as supplied) with excellent formulation stability.

SYNTRAN® 5905 is slowly added to the base product under agitation at the end of the manufacturing cycle (i.e., after final adjustment). A stability control is recommended.

data.name: SYNTRAN® 5288
data.description:
SYNTRAN® 5288 is based on a patented olefin grafted technology. An amorphous functional acrylic polymer section is grafted onto a crystalline polyethylene backbone. The crystalline portion provides barrier, moisture retention, elasticity, and tactile attributes such as lubricity and "feel". The amorphous portion provides film formation, adhesion, substantivity, and formulation flexibility.

The grafting technology results in a uniform film with the benefits of both chemistries. Its recommended use level is 5 to 55 percent as supplied.

data.name: SYNTRAN® EX149PE
data.description: SYNTRAN® EX149PE is a liquid solution consisting of a water-based styrene-acrylic polymer, serving as a dispersant primarily recommended for pigment dispersion. Adhering to standards like Credo Clean and Ulta Beauty's Conscious Beauty, it functions as a stabilizer and dispersing agent, offering benefits such as gloss enhancement, improved dispersion, low odor, ease of use, compatibility, strong hold, good wetting properties, and effective stabilization.

data.name: SYNTRAN® 5620CG
data.description:
SYNTRAN® 5620CG has been developed for advanced water-based nail polishes. Through a proprietary technology designated SAFE - a “State-of-the-art” Acrylate Film-forming Emulsion - ZSCHIMMER & SCHWARZ INTERPOLYMER offers an alternative to solvent based nail polishes.

Polishes based on SYNTRAN® 5620CG exhibit superior gloss, quick drying time, good water resistance, adequate hardness, excellent adhesion, and long-lasting wear properties.

data.name: SYNTRAN® KL219CG
data.description: SYNTRAN® KL219CG is a clear solution polymer in water with dispersing and film forming properties. The polymer is a good companion product to improve pigment dispersion, avoid aggregates, and solve the wetting issues. It enhances certain characteristics of the film such as leveling, gloss, hardness, and removability.

data.name: PROTELAN AG 915 SF
data.description: PROTELAN AG 915 SF stands as a fundamental ingredient for crafting bath preparations and hair shampoos. This liquid-form surfactant caters to skin cleansers and shampoos while complying with labeling standards such as credo clean, ulta beauty's conscious beauty, and clean at sephora. Committed to sustainability, it's labeled as solvent-free and derived from renewable resources. Its multifaceted benefits include a smooth feel, enhanced foam stiffness, moisturizing properties, and improved foam stability, ideal for rinse-off applications.

data.name: PROTELAN GG
data.description: PROTELAN GG is a liquid basic component used in crafting bath preparations and hair shampoos. It aligns with Credo Clean, Ulta Beauty's Conscious Beauty, and Clean at Sephora standards, functioning as a surfactant and anionic surfactant. With applications in skin cleansers and hair care products like shampoos and rinses, it is preservative-free and solvent-free, meeting REACH (Europe) standards. Noted for imparting a creamy texture, ensuring foam stability, and providing mild yet effective foaming for rinse-off applications.

data.name: PROTELAN PCA 40

summary.name: Synonyms
items: 2-Pyrrolidinone-5-carboxylic Acid Sodium Salt, 2-Pyrrolidone-5-carboxylic Acid Sodium Salt, 5-Carboxy-2-pyrrolidone Sodium Salt, L -Proline, 5-oxo-, Monosodium Salt, L -Proline, 5-oxo-, Sodium Salt, Monosodium L -pyroglutamate, Proline, 5-oxo-, Monosodium Salt, L -, Sodium 2-oxo-5-pyrrolidinecarboxylate, Sodium 2-pyrrolidinone-5-carboxylate, Sodium 2-pyrrolidone-5-carboxylate, Sodium L -pyroglutamate, Sodium L -pyrrolidonecarboxylate, Sodium Pidolate, Sodium Pyroglutamate, Sodium Pyrrolidone-5-carboxylate

data.description: PROTELAN PCA 40 functions as a humectant and aligns with various labeling standards like Credo Clean Standard, Ulta Beauty's Conscious Beauty, and Clean at Sephora. It's available in liquid form, typically as a carrier glycerin, making it suitable for leave-on applications like lotions and creams, as well as in bar soaps for bath and shower applications. Its versatility across different formats makes it an adaptable ingredient for various skincare products.

data.name: PROTELAN 1430

summary.name: Synonyms
items: N-Myristoylsarcosine acid sodium salt, N-Myristoylsarcosine sodium salt, Sodium myristoyl sarcosine, Sodium myristoylsarcosinate, Sodium N-myristoylsarcosinate, Sodium N-myristoylsarcosine

data.description: PROTELAN 1430 is applied as a mild co-surfactant for the manufacture of hair shampoos and bath preparations in order to improve the foam properties. PROTELAN 1430 accelerates the foam creation and improves the foam stability by forming very fine bubble. Compared to other surfactants PROTELAN 1430 shows very good foaming properties in the presence of the high concentrations of emollients or oils.

data.name: PROTELAN AG 8 - EC
data.description: PROTELAN AG 8 - EC, a basic material for bath preparations and hair shampoos, meets Credo Clean and Ulta Beauty's Conscious Beauty standards. As an anionic surfactant derived from renewable resources, certified organic by ECOCERT and COSMOS, it offers de-odorizing benefits, ideal for body washes, shampoos, and detergents. Its liquid form, free from preservatives, ensures foaming properties suitable for rinse-off applications in both household and industrial cleaning.

data.name: PROTELAN AGE

summary.name: Chemical Name
items: L-Glutamic acid, N-coco acyl derivs., disodium salts

data.description: PROTELAN AGE serves as a fundamental component for creating bath preparations and hair shampoos. It aligns with eco-conscious labeling and is a surfactant derived naturally. It also acts as an emulsifier, facilitating smooth and compatible textures in formulations. Its ingredients are sourced from vegetables, making it suitable for vegetarian products. This ingredient is particularly suitable for creating gentle and smooth baby bubble baths.

data.name: PROTELAN AGE - C

summary.name: Chemical Name
items: L-Glutamic acid, N-coco acyl derivs., disodium salts

data.description: PROTELAN AGE - C is a fundamental ingredient used in creating bath preparations and hair shampoos. This liquid surfactant and emulsifier, derived from natural, non-animal, and plant origins, is certified by ISO 16128 and COSMOS. Renowned for its smooth feel and compatibility, it's suitable for various applications including baby bubble baths, body washes, shampoos, and detergents, offering a preservative-free, foaming formulation ideal for rinse-off usage.

data.name: PROTELAN AGL 95
data.description: PROTELAN AGL 95 serves as a foundational element in creating bath preparations and hair shampoos, aligning with Ulta Beauty's Conscious Beauty standards. It functions as a surfactant, specifically an anionic surfactant, derived from natural, non-animal, and plant-based sources. Recognized for enhancing foam stiffness, it's suitable for various applications including baby bubble baths, body washes, shampoos, and detergents for home and industrial use. This liquid formulation is preservative-free and promotes effective foaming, imparting a non-oily and smooth feel after rinse-off.

data.name: PROTELAN AGL 95 - EC
data.description: PROTELAN AGL 95 - EC, a foundational material for bath preparations and hair shampoos, aligns with Credo Clean, Ulta Beauty's Conscious Beauty, and Clean at Sephora standards. This anionic surfactant, sodium N-lauroylglutamate, is naturally derived from non-animal, plant-based sources. Renowned for improving foam stiffness and offering a smooth, non-oily feel, it caters to various applications, including baby bubble baths, body washes, and shampoos. Its liquid form, free from preservatives, ensures compatibility and effective cleansing for both household and industrial uses.

data.name: PROTELAN AGL 95 – EC – RSPO – MB
data.description: PROTELAN AGL 95 – EC – RSPO – MB is basic material for the formulation of bath preparations and hair shampoos.

data.name: PROTELAN AGL 95 PV
data.description: PROTELAN AGL 95 PV acts as a core ingredient for bath preparations and hair shampoos, meeting standards like credo clean, ulta beauty's conscious beauty, and clean at sephora. This powder-form, naturally derived anionic surfactant—Sodium N-lauroylglutamate—is derived from plant origins. Renowned for enhancing foam stiffness, it's versatile for baby bubble baths, detergents, shampoos, and rinse-off applications, offering compatibility and beneficial properties like a non-oily, smooth feel in formulations free from preservatives

data.name: PROTELAN AG 37
data.description: PROTELAN AG 37 serves as a foundational ingredient for bath preparations and hair shampoos, meeting Credo Clean, Ulta Beauty's Conscious Beauty, and Clean at Sephora standards. In liquid form and free from propylene glycol and preservatives, it hails from renewable resources. This versatile ingredient functions as an emulsifier and surfactant, offering a spectrum of benefits, including a silky, light feel, emulsifying properties, non-drying effects, foam enhancement, a creamy texture, irritation reduction, and mild surfactant properties, ideal for rinse-off applications.
